===Etymology===
From {{etyl|sa}} [[अवतारः]] (avatāraḥ) via Hindustani [[अवतार]] / {{ur-Arab|[[اوتار]]}} (avatār), meaning "descent (of a [[deity]] from [[heaven]] in [[incarnate]] form)", from ''avatāriti'' "he descends": ''ava-'' "down" and ''tariti'' "(he) crosses".

